Ben Cox (thoth@netcom.com) wrote:

: Biham and Shamir looked at using an independent key for each round of
: DES in their work on differential cryptanalysis of DES[*], and found
: that increasing the key size in this way did not proportionally
: increase the time to break DES.  Unmodified (56-bit key), it took 2^47
: steps to break; modified for independent keys it took 2^64 steps.

Hmm.  I would have thought that 2^64 is a significant increase over 2^47.
